On Friday, July 15, 2005, at 02:50PM, <VWBrain(-at-)aol.com> wrote:

>  hey guys  I made my own holder many years ago and still use it   I
>  took a piece of metal block and some all thread  drilled two holes in
>  the metal block one the size so that the alltread would go thur and
>  one hole the size of the shaft of the dial indicator  . at the dial
>  indicator hole I drilled and tapped a hole perpendicular to it an
>  installed a set screw to hold the indicator  used two nuts on the
>  allthread to hold this in place  then used two nuts to mount it to the
>  block   I'll try to take a pix

There are also some plans in the Local Manufacture of Workshop Equipment
